Conditional code evaluates a condition and is executed if the expression evaluates to true. If you want to execute other code, you can put it inside an else block. Conditions can also be chained with if-else if - else.

A full example is:

if (height < 4) {
  print('Too short for this ride.');
} else if (height < 7) {
  print('Enjoy the ride!');
 } else {
   print('Too tall for this ride.');
}

Note: You can also have a single else statement or multipe else-if.

Work with your mentor to add 5-7 examples to your existing classes.

Sometimes, you have to handle a lot of different values for the same variable. A switch statement is an expressive way to do that.

Example:
switch (age) {
  case 16:
    print('You can drive a car now.');
  case 18:
    print('You can vote now!');
  default:
    print('Just enjoy your birthday!');
}

These often work really well with enums!


